h3. Summary
Our REST API documentation (https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/server/) does provide the schema of the response, but it can be improved to give more information of the response.

For example, the [Get Issue|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/server/#api/2/issue-getIssue] has the following response schema
{code}{
    "id": "https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/schema/issue#",
    "title": "Issue",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "expand": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "id": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "self": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "uri"
        },
        "key": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "fields": {
            "type": "object",
            "patternProperties": {
                ".+": {}
            },
            "additionalProperties": false
        },
        ...
        ...
        ...
    }
}{code}

This basically means that 'fields' can have any kind of property with any name, which isn't very useful.

h3. Suggestion
Improve the documentation to include more details such as what fields could be returned along with the types and properties, at least for system fields which would always be returned.

The same should be applied for all other response schema. If there are any items which would always be returned, include those in the documentation

h3. Problem Definition
Currently empty JQL returns all existing issues you have permission to. 
This might lead to performance problems at busy instance. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Add an option for JIRA Administrator to change to default behaviour of *empty JQL*, it will return no data. 

h3. Workaround 
* Proactive - Check DB for filters with empty JQL. 
{code:SQL|borderStyle=solid}
select * from searchrequest where length(reqcontent) < 3 or reqcontent is NULL;
{code}
* Check empty JQL +'*:*'+ in logs, from {{atlassian-jira-slow-queries.log}}, eg:
{noformat}
2017-05-28 21:40:56,154 Caesium-1-3 INFO     [c.a.j.i.search.providers.LuceneSearchProvider_SLOW] JQL query 'order by updated DESC' produced lucene query '*:*' and took '2090' ms to run

2017-11-10 10:08:53,351 ajp-nio-8009-exec-3301 user INFO  608x29513053x25 1cx9voq /secure/ConfigureReport.jspa [c.a.j.i.search.providers.LuceneSearchProvider_SLOW] JQL query '' produced lucene query '*:*' and took '10353' ms to run.
{noformat}

h3.Summary
The REST API for creating a project category {{/rest/api/latest/projectCategory}} requires the "Description" field; although the UI does not require this field when creating a project category.

h3.Steps to Reproduce
Create a POST request to {{$jira-url/rest/api/latest/projectCategory}}, with the data set to:
{code}
{"name":"Support"}
{code}

h3.Expected Results
The project category is created successfully.

h3.Actual Results
The project category is not created successfully - the REST API returns an error 400; along with the message {{Input parameter 'description' was not provided}}.

h3.Workaround
Include the "Description" field, as below:

{code}
{"name":"The Name","description":"The Description"}
{code}
